data.chText: 呻吟
data.enText: to make a long deep sound, usually expressing unhappiness, suffering or sexual pleasure

data.chText: 痛苦地呻吟
data.enText: to moan in/with pain

data.chText: 受伤的人躺在地上呻吟着。
data.enText: The injured man was lying on the ground, moaning.

data.chText: 她呻吟着说：“我可能再也见不到你了。”
data.enText: ‘I might never see you again,’ she moaned.

data.chText: 抱怨
data.enText: to complain about sth in a way that other people find annoying

data.chText: 你在抱怨什么呢？
data.enText: What are you moaning on about now?

data.chText: 他们总是牢骚满腹，抱怨有很多事要做。
data.enText: They're always moaning and groaning about how much they have to do.

data.chText: 贝拉抱怨说她的脚冷。
data.enText: Bella moaned that her feet were cold.

data.chText: 呼啸；发出萧萧声
data.enText: to make a long deep sound

data.chText: 呻吟声
data.enText: a long deep sound, usually expressing unhappiness, suffering or sexual pleasure

data.chText: 在绝望 / 痛苦中发出的低沉的呻吟声
data.enText: a low moan of despair/anguish

data.chText: 抱怨
data.enText: a complaint about sth

data.chText: 我们对工作大大地抱怨了一番。
data.enText: We had a good moan about work.

data.chText: 他的来信总是满纸怨言。
data.enText: His letters are full of the usual moans and groans.

data.chText: （尤指风的）呼啸声，萧萧声
data.enText: a long deep sound, especially the sound that is made by the wind

data.text: complain ♦ protest ♦ object ♦ grumble ♦ moan ♦ whine ♦ whinge

data.chText: 以上各词均含对人或事物感到恼怒、不高兴或不满之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about sb/sth.
complain

data.chText: 指抱怨、埋怨、发牢骚：
data.enText: to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about sb/sth

data.chText: 我要就这件事给经理提意见。
data.enText: I'm going to complain to the manager about this.
protest

data.chText: 指公开反对、抗议或申辩：
data.enText: to say or do sth to show that you disagree with or disapprove of sth, especially publicly; to give sth as a reason for protesting

data.chText: 学生走上街头抗议这项决定。
data.enText: Students took to the streets to protest against the decision.
object

data.chText: 指不同意、不赞成、反对或抗辩：
data.enText: to say that you disagree with or disapprove of sth; to give sth as a reason for objecting

data.chText: 如果没有人反对，我们就把会议推迟到下周。
data.enText: If nobody objects, we'll postpone the meeting till next week.

data.chText: 他抗辩说警察没有充分证据就逮捕了他。
data.enText: He objected that the police had arrested him without sufficient evidence.
grumble

data.chText: 指咕哝、嘟囔、发牢骚：
data.enText: ( rather informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in a bad-tempered way

data.chText: 他们不停地嘟囔着说冷。
data.enText: They kept grumbling that they were cold.
moan

data.chText: 指抱怨、埋怨：
data.enText: ( BrE , rather informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in an annoying way

data.chText: 你在抱怨什么呢？
data.enText: What are you moaning on about now?
whine

data.chText: 指哭哭啼啼或哭嚷着诉说：
data.enText: ( rather informal , disapproving ) to complain in an annoying, crying voice

data.chText: 别哭哭啼啼的！
data.enText: Stop whining!

data.chText: “我要回家。”托比哼哼唧唧地说。
data.enText: ‘I want to go home,’ whined Toby.

data.chText: whine通常用于小孩子抱怨。
data.enText: Whine is often used to talk about the way that young children complain.
whinge

data.chText: 指絮絮叨叨地抱怨：
data.enText: ( BrE , informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in an annoying way

data.chText: 她总是嘟囔着说一切都太不公平了。
data.enText: She's always whingeing about how unfair everything is.

data.chText: 用grumble、moan还是whinge？
以上三词均为complain的非正式用词。grumble表达抱怨者的感受，即心情不好；moan和whinge多表达听者的心情，即抱怨使人心烦。
data.enText: These are all fairly informal words for ‘complain’. Grumble tells you how the person who is complaining feels (= they are in a bad mood) ; moan and whinge tell you more about how the people listening to the complaints feel (= the complaining is annoying them) .
grumble, moan or whinge ?
to complain/protest/grumble/moan/whine/whinge about sth
to complain/protest/grumble/moan at sth
to complain/protest/object/grumble/moan/whine/whinge to sb
to complain/protest/object/grumble/moan/whine that…
to complain/protest/object bitterly

ex.chText: 她看着窗外，为自己失去的青春而叹息。
ex.enText: She looked out of the window, sighing for her lost youth.

ex.chText: 他旁边的妇女没回答，深深地叹了一口气。
ex.enText: The lady next to him didn't answer and sighed deeply.
What made him sigh with relief?

synonyms.bx: 指因厌烦、失望、疲惫等而发出叹气声。

ex.chText: 病人被抬上担架时在痛苦地呻吟着。
ex.enText: The patient groaned painfully as he was lifted onto the stretcher.
He lay on the bed groaning.

ex.chText: 被她亲了一口，他愉快地哼哼着。
ex.enText: As she kissed him, he groaned with pleasure.

synonyms.bx: 多指因疼痛、心烦、失望等而呻吟，有时也指因快乐而哼哼。

ex.chText: 那个生病的女人在痛苦地呻吟。
ex.enText: The sick woman moaned in pain.

synonyms.bx: 指因疼痛、郁闷、激情等而发出长而低沉的声音。

tr: an utterance expressing pain or disapproval

example: The students groaned when the professor got out the exam booklets
The ancient door soughed when opened

value.def: If you moan, you make a low sound, usually because you are unhappy or in pain.

example.ex: Tony moaned in his sleep and then turned over on his side...
example.tran: 托尼在睡梦中发出呻吟声，然后翻了个身。

example.ex: 'My head, my head,' he moaned. 'I can't see.'
example.tran: “我的头，我的头，”他呻吟着说，“我看不见了。”

example.ex: Suddenly she gave a low, choking moan and began to tremble violently.
example.tran: 突然，她发出了一声低沉而哽咽的呻吟，然后剧烈地颤抖起来。

value.def: To moan means to complain or speak in a way which shows that you are very unhappy.

example.ex: I used to moan if I didn't get at least six hours' sleep at night.
example.tran: 过去如果晚上的睡眠时间不足6小时的话，我就会抱怨。

example.ex: They moan on a lot about money...
example.tran: 他们对钱的事情抱怨不已。
梅格抱怨道：“我不想这样！”

example.ex: The gardener was moaning that he had another garden to do later that morning.
example.tran: 园丁当时抱怨说，上午晚些时候他还要到另一个花园干活。

example.ex: They have been listening to people's gripes, moans and praise.
example.tran: 他们一直在倾听人们的牢骚、抱怨和表扬。

value.def: If you have a moan, you complain about something.

example.ex: You can go see him and have a good old moan.
example.tran: 你可以去看看他，好好地诉诉苦。

example.ex: ...the occasional moan of the wind round the corners of the house.
example.tran: 风刮过屋角时间或发出的呼啸声
远处车流传来的低沉的嘈杂声
